Figure 2c, d show the 128 pixel-averaged VCPD for parts of each BLR of TB-H2Pc/PTCBI/ITO and TB-PTCBI/H2Pc/ITO, respectively, and the VCPD values are 0.54 V and −0.02 V. The φsample values were estimated using Eq. (2) as φH2Pc/PTCBI = 4.38 eV and φPTCBI/H2Pc = 4.94 eV. These VCPD and φsample values are very different from those of single layers and imply an effect on the OSM as a substrate. Notably, the differences of the φsample values between the single and BLRs are coincidently 0.2 V for both cases; i.e.,3φH2Pc∕PTCBI-φPTCBI≈-0.2eV\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
