The dot terraced bilayer H2Pc/PTCBI/Teflon membrane was prepared with a diameter of each H2Pc dot = 200 µm, pitch = 200 µm. Membrane size ≈0.6 cm × 0.6 cm. The thickness of both the PTCBI and H2Pc was 50 nm. The control sample was a container without any film that was kept under the dark condition. Light irradiation was from the H2Pc side. The irradiation time was 1 h. The result from the gas chromatography analysis is shown for the amount of CO2 evolution (in mol) and EQE (in %). The amount of CO2 in the blank sample was 0.02 µmol, and the value was zeroed to be the baseline value for the bilayer and the dot TB samples
